Electro-optronic equipment makers&lt;United Scientific Holdings Plc> said the Advanced ProductsDivision of its U.S. Subsidiary &lt;OEC Dallas, Texas> has beenawarded a 4.3 mln dlr contract by the U.S. Army.    The contract is for the production of high energy laserprotection filters for binoculars. The three year contractalready includes options to the value of eight mln dlrs.    United reported pretax profit of 3.2 mln stg on turnover of117.9 mln stg in the year ended September 1986. The company'sshares were unchanged on Friday's close of 243p followingtoday's announcement.    REUTER&#3;